features: PLAY AS STORM: Storm is an Egyptian goddess with the mutant ability to control the weather at will. Kids can imagine scouting the skies as Storm while cruising in the X-Men Team X-Jet! This Marvel toy set features a 4-inch action figure, vehicle, and accessories
X-JET WITH ACTION FEATURES: Jet toy includes 2 projectiles for blast action fun and a drop-down hero swing where Storm figure can hang from. Open X-Jet's cockpit to place figure inside!

X-JET DOUBLES AS CARRIER: Discover even more exciting action play by using X-Jet as a cruisin' carrier for Storm! Place action figure on stand in the back of the jet and imagine defeating enemies with awesome moves

TOYS FOR X-MEN FANS AND KIDS ALIKE: Look out for other toys inspired by Marvel Studios X-Men '97! Toys make great gifts for kids, new fans, and longtime fans of the series. (Each sold separately. Subject to availability.)
body.description: Command the elements and roam the skies with the Marvel Studios X-Men '97 X-Men Team X-Jet and Storm set! This Marvel toy includes a 4 inch action figure and toy jet designed and inspired by the classic show series. Storm figure features 9 points of articulation for epic action poses during playtime. Figure comes with 2 detachable accessories for even more imaginative, action-packed fun! X-Men Team X-Jet has a blast action feature and includes 2 projectiles that kids can load into both sides of vehicle! Jet's cockpit can open and close to place figure inside. Jet also has a drop-down swing that kids can hang the figure from. Storm figure can be placed on stand on the back of the jet so kids can imagine this powerful super hero cruisin' and stormin' into action in the skies!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 5, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars A good solid figure and vehicle at sale price... over priced at original cost.
reviews.reviewText: The X-Jet at first glance seems way to small, but then it grows on you. I still wish it was a little bigger to fit two figures in the cockpit instead if just one, and I wish the rear extended out a bit more. With that being said it still looks really cool and I like it overall.The Storm figure is what brings this purchase together. The fact that she comes included is truly awesome because these days action figure lines don't often include a figure with their vehicles, at least not as much as they did in the 80s. Storm is a good size, a well made figure, and a good quality sculpt.The original price is way to high though ($34.99) and it isn't worth it in my opinion at that price. However I grabbed it at the sale price ($15.83). That is a more than reasonable price and if you can get it for that I say jump at it. A good solid set overall and I am pleased with my purchase.
